%% seq_10_org_join_request.mmd
%% Scope: Organization join request lifecycle (submit → pending → approve/reject)
%% Backend refs:
%%   - GET/POST /organizations/:id/join → JoinOrganizationController
%%     → CheckJoinEligibilityQuery + CreateJoinRequestCommand
%%   - GET /organizations/:id/members/pending → PendingRequestsController
%%     → GetPendingRequestsQuery
%%   - POST /organizations/:id/members/process-request/:userId
%%     → ProcessJoinRequestController → ProcessJoinRequestCommand
%%   - ⚠️ v3.0 uses organization_users (status='pending') NOT organization_join_requests
%%   - ⚠️ Transmit transport=null (no WebSocket)

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as User (Requester)
    participant B as Browser (Svelte)
    participant C as Controller
    participant Q as Query
    participant Cmd as Command
    participant Entity as Domain Entity
    participant Repo as Repository
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    actor Admin as Org Owner/Admin

    Note over User, Admin: === CHECK ELIGIBILITY + SUBMIT ===
    Note over C: JoinOrganizationController
    Note over C: GET shows join page
    Note over C: POST submits request

    User->>B: Visit organization page
    B->>C: GET /organizations/:id/join
    C->>Q: CheckJoinEligibilityQuery.execute(dto)
    Q->>Repo: findMembership(orgId, userId)
    Repo->>DB: SELECT FROM organization_users
    WHERE organization_id=? AND user_id=?
    DB-->>Repo: Result
    Note over Repo: Infra Mapper: ORM Model → Domain Entity
    Repo-->>Q: Membership entity or null

    alt Already approved member
        Q-->>C: Not eligible: already_member
        C-->>B: Show "Already a member"
    else Has pending request (status='pending')
        Q-->>C: Not eligible: pending_request
        C-->>B: Show "Request pending"
    else Eligible
        C-->>B: Show join form
        User->>B: Enter message + submit
        B->>C: POST /organizations/:id/join
        C->>Cmd: CreateJoinRequestCommand.execute(dto)
        Note over Cmd: App Mapper: Request DTO → Domain params
        Note over Cmd: v3.0: Creates/updates
        Note over Cmd: organization_users row
        Note over Cmd: with status='pending'
        Note over Cmd: NOT organization_join_requests
        Cmd->>Entity: OrganizationUser.create(orgId,<br/>userId, role='org_member', status='pending')
        Note over Entity: Domain validation
        Cmd->>Repo: save(membershipEntity)
        Note over Repo: Infra Mapper: Domain Entity → ORM Model
        Repo->>DB: INSERT INTO organization_users
        (organization_id, user_id,
        org_role='org_member',
        status='pending')
        DB-->>Repo: Created
        Repo-->>Cmd: Persisted entity
        Cmd->>Cmd: emit('audit:log')
        Cmd-->>C: OK
        C-->>B: Redirect with success message
    end

    Note over User, Admin: === VIEW PENDING REQUESTS ===
    Note over C: PendingRequestsController

    Admin->>B: Open pending requests
    B->>C: GET /organizations/:id/members/pending
    C->>Q: GetPendingRequestsQuery.execute(dto)
    Q->>Repo: findPendingMembers(orgId)
    Repo->>DB: SELECT ou.*, u.*
    FROM organization_users ou
    JOIN users u ON ou.user_id = u.id
    WHERE ou.organization_id = ?
    AND ou.status = 'pending'
    DB-->>Repo: Result set
    Note over Repo: Infra Mapper: ORM Models → Domain Entities
    Repo-->>Q: Pending member entities
    Note over Q: App Mapper: Domain Entities → Response DTOs
    Q-->>C: Pending list
    C-->>B: Render pending page
    B-->>Admin: Show requests

    Note over User, Admin: === APPROVE / REJECT ===
    Note over C: ProcessJoinRequestController

    Admin->>B: Click Approve or Reject
    B->>C: POST /organizations/:id/members/process-request/:userId
    (body: { action: 'approve' | 'reject' })

    C->>Cmd: ProcessJoinRequestCommand.execute(dto)
    Cmd->>Repo: findPendingMembership(orgId, userId)
    Repo->>DB: SELECT FROM organization_users
    WHERE organization_id=? AND user_id=?
    AND status='pending'
    DB-->>Repo: Result
    Note over Repo: Infra Mapper: ORM Model → Domain Entity
    Repo-->>Cmd: Membership entity

    alt action = 'approve'
        Cmd->>Entity: membership.approve(processedBy=admin.id)
        Note over Entity: Row already exists,
        Note over Entity: no need to INSERT
        Cmd->>Repo: save(membershipEntity)
        Note over Repo: Infra Mapper: Domain Entity → ORM Model
        Repo->>DB: UPDATE organization_users
        SET status='approved',
        processed_by=admin.id
    else action = 'reject'
        Cmd->>Entity: membership.reject(processedBy=admin.id)
        Cmd->>Repo: save(membershipEntity)
        Note over Repo: Infra Mapper: Domain Entity → ORM Model
        Repo->>DB: UPDATE organization_users
        SET status='rejected',
        processed_by=admin.id
    end

    Cmd-->>C: OK
    C-->>B: Redirect back

